@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "How to Start Blogging in 2025";
}

<div class="content blog-content">
    <h1 class="mb-3"><span style="font-weight: bold;">How to Start Blogging in 2025</span></h1>
    <img src="~/images/blog-start-2025.jpg" alt="Blogging 2025" class="img-fluid rounded mb-4" />

    <p class="lead">
        Blogging in 2025 is more than just writing — it’s about creating experiences. With evolving platforms, AI-powered tools, and smarter audiences, here’s how you can kickstart your blog journey.
    </p>

    <h4>1. Choose Your Niche</h4>
    <p>
        Pick a topic you’re passionate about — whether it’s tech, travel, food, or finance. Focus is key.
    </p>

    <h4>2. Build Your Brand</h4>
    <p>
        Choose a unique name, design a recognizable logo, and maintain a consistent tone of voice.
    </p>

    <h4>3. Use AI Tools Wisely</h4>
    <p>
        From generating blog ideas to proofreading content, AI tools like Grammarly and ChatGPT can enhance your writing speed and quality.
    </p>

    <h4>4. Focus on SEO</h4>
    <p>
        Learn basic SEO to optimize your content for search engines — proper headings, meta descriptions, and keyword research matter.
    </p>

    <h4>5. Publish Consistently</h4>
    <p>
        Create a content calendar and post regularly. Readers love reliability.
    </p>

    <h4>6. Engage With Your Audience</h4>
    <p>
        Reply to comments, post on social media, and build a community around your blog.
    </p>

    <h4>7. Monetize Your Blog</h4>
    <p>
        Affiliate marketing, sponsored posts, and digital products can help you turn your blog into a business.
    </p>
</div>

<script>
    setTimeout(() => {
        if (!sessionStorage.getItem('registerPromptShown')) {
            const shouldRedirect = confirm("Love writing? Join BlogVerse and share your journey. Want to register?");
            if (shouldRedirect) {
                window.location.href = "/Account/Register";
            }
            sessionStorage.setItem('registerPromptShown', 'true');
        }
    }, 3000);
</script>